<br>
Since I started playing EQ, I have emailed EQ incessantly about making an RP server. In my travels of Norrath, I have encountered but scant few who role-played and it was like a breath of fresh air meeting them! After playing on the test server where the majority of players were at least attempting a characterization, I am excited it and see great potential for us!<br>
<br>
I am also dismayed by the players whose sole purpose in life seems to be to use any new server in the race for Uber-ness. (What is that? The first one to God-status wins????) I say JUST SAY *NO*!<br>
<br>
YOU WANT TO KEEP THE RP SERVER CLEAN OF THE EQUIPMENT-MOBSTERS AND UBER-MONGERS?<br>
<br>
-IGNORE them!  If you don't hear any character development in their conversation walk away! By all means, this should go for players who use phrases such as, &quot;can u sow plz.&quot;<br>
<br>
-DON'T BUY anything from Equipment-mobsters! You will know them by what they sell at early points in the game! The server is open for two days and someone is selling Fine Steel Weapons?<br>
<br>
-Don't group with kewl-d00ds! The minute you hear them talking about *phat lewt* in group or have no clue what RPing or characterization is,  disband, DISband, DISBAND! Kick out the loser and reform the group if necessary! <br>
<br>
-Don't TALK to them. The minute you hear them talking OOC in auction or shouts put them on your IGNORE list immediately.  <br>
<br>
The more of us who refuse to cater to the  whim of these *uber-mongers* who have no intention of RPing, the more likely these ill-begottens will give up and go elsewhere. <br>
They can't be a kewl-d00d in a vaccum now can they? <br>
<br>
Feel free to post other ideas for supporting RPing and not Uber-mongers.<br>
<br>
